<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="704" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 362.115H21/2</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-27">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.45 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="italic">Leelanaw</hi> crew proceeding to Dundee. Captain
                                torpedoed ship states agent Kirkwall he had ample time leave his
                                ship before being fired on. Crew went on board submarine and
                                remained some time, ship’s boats being taken in tow for about fifty
                                miles.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>